        "body_content": "\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nHero card Home charging V10 wo MSRP\n\n\nHOME\nCHARGING\n\nProCharging@ford.com 1-800-34-FLEET\n\nFleet-focused home charging solutions \nequipped with 25 �. cable enabling parking \nflexibility for fleet vehicles \n\nCommercial-grade Hardware\n\nAllows drivers to continue taking their work\nvehicles home, reducing everyday driving time\nand cost.\nSimplifies home charger installation and tracking \nacross your take-home fleet\n\nBenefits of \nHome Charging\n\nHome Installation,\nSimplified\n\nProvides access to a vetted and insured installer \nnetwork and supports managing multiple home instal-\nlations simultaneously via our supplier, Qmerit.\nReceive one consolidated bill covering multiple \ninstalls\nBacked by 3-Year Warranty2\n\nFull-service concierge installation option Includes:\n Hardware Shipment\n Scheduling Coordination\n Home Installation\n\nTools for home energy use reimbursement \nreporting via Ford ProTM E-Telematics1 on\nFord vehicles.\n\nIntegrated So�ware\n\nFleet vehicle owners can power up their \nvehicles from the comfort of their home \nwith charging hardware and so�ware that \nmakes operations easy for drivers and\nfleet managers.\n\nEasily track and manage driver reimbursement \nreports for home energy use via Ford ProTM\n\nE-Telematics  1 for Ford Vehicles  \nReimbursement reporting included for three years \non all Ford fleet electric vehicles1 \n\nReporting only captures charging events for regis-\ntered fleet vehicles. Non-fleet vehicle charging \nevents are excluded from reimbursement reports.\n\nManagement Tools\nThat Make Sense \n\nPreproduction model shown. 2022 F-150 Lightning production begins spring 2022.\nFleet con�guration only, not available for retail sale. Fleet sales require an eligible FIN, see a �eet sales specialist for details.\n\n\n\nFord Charge Station Pro (19.2kW)\n\n240V Connector \n\nMax Output Current 80A (requires 100A circuit) \n\n15-100% charge in 8 hours (F-150&reg; LightningTM Pro\nExtended-Range Battery)3\n\nWorks with all EVs that use US standard charging\nconnectors   or adaptors (CCS1)\n\nIncludes 25 �. cord\nFinancing options available through Ford ProTM FinSimpleTM\n\nCommercial Grade Enclosure\nPrimary Use Case: Overnight charge\n\nWi-Fi and Bluetooth capable \n\nInstallation by licensed electrician required\n\nBacked by 3-Year Warranty2\n\nH\nO\n\nM\nE \n\nIN\nST\n\nA\nLL\n\n C\nH\n\nA\nRG\n\nER\nS\n\nQmerit is a Ford Pro home installation supplier. Full-service concierge installation services (for up to 80A/240V \ncharging solutions) are available for fleet home customers. To learn more about the home install program reach out \nvia email to procharging@ford.com or call 1-800-34-FLEET.\n\nFord ProTM + Qmerit : Our Trusted Supplier for Home Installation Services \n\n2 The Limited Warranty is being provided by Ford to the person or entity who purchased the Product from Ford (&ldquo;Buyer&rdquo;) and, subject to the product terms and conditions, covers any defect in the Product which can be directly and exclusively attributed to design, workmanship or \nmaterial defect of the Product for a period of three (3) years (the &ldquo;Warranty Period&rdquo;) a�er the Warranty Starting Date (as herea�er defined). The &ldquo;Warranty Starting Date&rdquo; is the date that is the earlier of: (i) the date the Product is installed at the Buyer&rsquo;s site; or (ii) the date that is six (6) \nmonths a�er the date the Product is shipped to Buyer. \n3 Charge time based on manufacturer computer engineering simulations. The charging rate decreases as battery reaches full capacity. Your results may vary based on peak charging times and battery state of charge.\n\n1 Eligible vehicles receive a complimentary three-year trial of E-Telematics services that begins on the new vehicle warranty start date. Requires modem activation. Terms and conditions apply. Telematics service and features, and access to vehicle data depend on compatible AT&amp;T \nnetwork availability. Evolving technology/cellular networks availability. Evolving technology/cellular networks/vehicle capability may limit functionality and prevent operation of connected features. A�er the three-year trial, annual service contract is required for E-Telematics service. Go \nto fleetaccount.ford.com or 1-833-811-3673 to activate E-Telematics service.  \n\nFord Pro AC Charging Station (11.5kW)\n\n240V Connector \n\nMax Output Current 48A (requires 60A circuit)  \n\n0-100% charge in 8 hours (E-Transit)3\n\nWorks with all EVs that use US standard charging\nconnectors or adaptors (J1772) \n\n15-100% charge in 10 hours (F-150&reg; LightningTM Pro\nStandard-Range Battery)3\n\nIncludes 25 �. cord\n\nPrimary Use Case: Overnight charge  \n\nCommercial Grade Enclosure\n\nCellular &amp; Wi-Fi capable\n\nBacked by 3-Year Warranty2\n\nInstallation by licensed electrician required \n\nFinancing options available through Ford ProTM FinSimpleTM\n\n\n",
